This patch expands what were previously hidden tuple patterns inside enum element patterns that match a case with associated values.  For example:

```swift
enum X {
  case y(bool)
}

switch X.y(true) {
  case .y: ()
}
```

`case .y` used to be typechecked as an enum element pattern with no sub-pattern.  Now, it will be typechecked as `case .y(_)`.

This allows the elimination of corner cases in the Space Engine and fixes the size heuristic in the case of large sub-patterns that were being omitted by the user in a pattern match.
